<http://drug.uk/usage/renal-impairment/8e69836c-5152-43f4-856f-3cae8c877217> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> " Dose adjustments\nIn adults:\n1 g initially, then 500 mg every 12 hours if eGFR 26–50 mL/minute/1.73 m^2.\n1 g initially, then 500 mg every 24 hours if eGFR 11–26 mL/minute/1.73 m^2.\n1 g initially, then 500 mg every 36 hours if eGFR less than 11 mL/minute/1.73 m^2.\nIn children:\nReduce dose if estimated glomerular filtration rate less than 50 mL/minute/1.73 m^2" .
